underts und ihre Sicht auf die westliche und islamische Philosophiegeschichte vorgestellt. Zugleich wird der Einfluss ihres Denkens auf den vorrevolutionären Iran aufgezeigt.  aThe contentious engagement with Western thought is one of the focal points of Iranian intellectual life. This volume examines two major figures in 20th century Iranian intellectual history, Muhammad Husayn Tabatabaí (1903–1981) and Mortaza Motahhari (1920–1979), and presents their historical views on Western and Islamic philosophy. It also describes the impact of their ideas on pre-revolutionary Iranian thinking.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aGeistesgeschichte. 4aIntellektuellengeschichte. 4aIran. 4aislamische Philosophie. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Egypt (see also Ancient / Egypt).2bisacsh  aIntellectual history.  aIslamic philosophy.  ahistory of ideas.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103928070 cprintz978311037515240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036993940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110369939423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110369939/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014